<DOC><DOCNO> AP880526-0091 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-26-88 0810EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-People-O'Toole     05-26 0174</FIRST><SECOND>PM-People-O'Toole,0182</SECOND><HEAD>Peter O'Toole Returns To U.S. To Decide Custody Of Son</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The 5-year-old son of actor Peter O'Toolereturned from London with his American mother pending a decision onwhich parent should have custody.   Karen Somerville of Middleton Township, N.J., and her son,Lorcan, arrived at Kennedy International Airport on Wednesday.   ``They're very happy to be with each other,'' said Raoul Felder,Ms. Somerville's lawyer.   The Irish-born O'Toole, 55, had taken the boy on a visit toBritain and refused to return him in early May, lawyers for Ms.Somerville said.   The 37-year-old former model, who took the actor's name but wasnever married to him, received a court order in London on Tuesdayrequiring O'Toole to return the boy pending a court hearing in NewJersey on June 14.   The couple have been fighting over their son since they partedin 1983, and a New Jersey court had given them joint custody.   O'Toole is known for such films as ``Lawrence of Arabia'' and``The Lion in Winter.''</TEXT></DOC>